{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.40",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 40,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 40",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 40 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:1",
      "text": "Moreover Yahweh answered Job,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:2",
      "text": "“Shall he who argues contend with the Almighty? He who argues with God, let him answer it.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:3",
      "text": "Then Job answered Yahweh,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:4",
      "text": "“Behold, I am of small account. What will I answer you? I lay my hand on my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:5",
      "text": "I have spoken once, and I will not answer; Yes, twice, but I will proceed no further.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:6",
      "text": "Then Yahweh answered Job out of the whirlwind:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:7",
      "text": "“Now brace yourself like a man. I will question you, and you will answer me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:8",
      "text": "Will you even annul my judgment? Will you condemn me, that you may be justified?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:9",
      "text": "Or do you have an arm like God? Can you thunder with a voice like him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:10",
      "text": "“Now deck yourself with excellency and dignity. Array yourself with honor and majesty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:11",
      "text": "Pour out the fury of your anger. Look at everyone who is proud, and bring him low.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:12",
      "text": "Look at everyone who is proud, and humble him. Crush the wicked in their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:13",
      "text": "Hide them in the dust together. Bind their faces in the hidden place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:14",
      "text": "Then I will also admit to you that your own right hand can save you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:15",
      "text": "“See now behemoth, which I made as well as you. He eats grass as an ox.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:16",
      "text": "Look now, his strength is in his thighs. His force is in the muscles of his belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:17",
      "text": "He moves his tail like a cedar. The sinews of his thighs are knit together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:18",
      "text": "His bones are like tubes of bronze. His limbs are like bars of iron.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:19",
      "text": "He is the chief of the ways of God. He who made him gives him his sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:20",
      "text": "Surely the mountains produce food for him, where all the animals of the field play.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:21",
      "text": "He lies under the lotus trees, in the covert of the reed, and the marsh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:22",
      "text": "The lotuses cover him with their shade. The willows of the brook surround him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:23",
      "text": "Behold, if a river overflows, he doesn’t tremble. He is confident, though the Jordan swells even to his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.40.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 40,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 40:24",
      "text": "Shall any take him when he is on the watch, or pierce through his nose with a snare?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
